<subSubSection id="C34D65505C6DFFBEFF38FDB5FB47FCE2" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BE836DB5C6DFFBEFF38FDB5FA71FD38" blockId="36.[151,1436,592,879]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Diagnosis: Pronotum completely covered by setae (best seen in lateral view), setae arising directly from the surface. Male ectoproct with ventromedial lobe not sclerotized. Gonarcal membrane without scales. Male with pores at tergites IV and V (most specimens with pores at tergite III, too). Spermatheca widening distally.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE836DB5C6DFFBEFF69FD25FB47FCE2" blockId="36.[151,1436,592,879]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<bibRefCitation id="EFC64B2A5C6DFFBEFF69FD25FE6EFD56" author="Hoffman" box="[198,388,704,730]" firstAuthor="Hoffman" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" pagination="251 - 275" refId="ref30681" refString="Hoffman, K. M. (2002) Family Mantispidae. In Penny, N. D. (ed.), A guide to the lacewings (Neuroptera) of Costa Rica. Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, 53 (12), 251 - 275." type="journal article" year="2002">Hoffman (2002)</bibRefCitation>
stated that there were eight species in the genus but listed only three. 
<taxonomicName id="4C574D585C6DFFBEFB00FD25FF34FD73" authority="(Banks, 1912)" baseAuthorityName="Banks" baseAuthorityYear="1912" class="Insecta" family="Mantispidae" genus="Mantispilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulchella">
<emphasis id="B923EAC95C6DFFBEFB00FD25FAD1FD55" box="[1199,1339,704,729]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">L. pulchella</emphasis>
(Banks, 1912)
</taxonomicName>
is found from 
<collectingCountry id="F340764B5C6DFFBEFE37FD00FE19FD73" box="[408,499,741,767]" name="Canada" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Canada</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry id="F340764B5C6DFFBEFDB3FD00FD48FD73" box="[540,674,741,767]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFC64B2A5C6DFFBEFD1BFD00FBE5FD73" author="Cannings &amp; Cannings" box="[692,1039,741,767]" firstAuthor="Cannings" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" pagination="531 - 544" refId="ref30438" refString="Cannings, R. A. &amp; Cannings, S. G. (2006) The Mantispidae (Insecta: Neuroptera) of Canada, with notes on morphology, ecology, and distribution. The Canadian Entomologist, 138, 531 - 544." type="journal article" year="2006">Cannings &amp; Cannings 2006</bibRefCitation>
), remaing two species (
<taxonomicName id="4C574D585C6DFFBEFA9BFD00FEBBFCA8" authority="Hoffman, 2002" authorityName="Hoffman" authorityYear="2002" class="Insecta" family="Mantispidae" genus="Leptomantispa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chaos">
<emphasis id="B923EAC95C6DFFBEFA9BFD00FA71FD72" box="[1332,1435,741,766]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">L. chaos</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC64B2A5C6DFFBEFF38FCEFFEBBFCA8" author="Hoffman" box="[151,337,778,804]" firstAuthor="Hoffman" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" pagination="251 - 275" refId="ref30681" refString="Hoffman, K. M. (2002) Family Mantispidae. In Penny, N. D. (ed.), A guide to the lacewings (Neuroptera) of Costa Rica. Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, 53 (12), 251 - 275." type="journal article" year="2002">Hoffman, 2002</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C574D585C6DFFBEFE3FFCEFFD3DFCA8" authority="Hoffman, 2002" authorityName="Hoffman" authorityYear="2002" box="[400,727,778,804]" class="Insecta" family="Mantispidae" genus="Leptomantispa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nymphe">
<emphasis id="B923EAC95C6DFFBEFE3FFCEFFDFAFCAF" box="[400,528,778,803]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">L. nymphe</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC64B2A5C6DFFBEFDB6FCEFFD3DFCA8" author="Hoffman" box="[537,727,778,804]" firstAuthor="Hoffman" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" pagination="251 - 275" refId="ref30681" refString="Hoffman, K. M. (2002) Family Mantispidae. In Penny, N. D. (ed.), A guide to the lacewings (Neuroptera) of Costa Rica. Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, 53 (12), 251 - 275." type="journal article" year="2002">Hoffman, 2002</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
) are Neotropical and found in 
<collectingCountry id="F340764B5C6DFFBEFBF9FCEFFB4FFCA8" box="[1110,1189,778,804]" name="Brazil" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. Machado &amp; Rafael (2007) described a fourth species of the genus, 
<taxonomicName id="4C574D585C6DFFBEFD10FCD5FCA4FCC5" authorityName="Machado &amp; Rafael" authorityYear="2007" box="[703,846,816,841]" class="Insecta" family="Mantispidae" genus="Leptomantispa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="catarinae">
<emphasis id="B923EAC95C6DFFBEFD10FCD5FCA4FCC5" box="[703,846,816,841]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">L. catarinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, until now found only in 
<collectingCountry id="F340764B5C6DFFBEFBD7FCD5FB29FCC6" box="[1144,1219,816,842]" name="Brazil" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. More two species are treated here: 
<taxonomicName id="4C574D585C6DFFBEFEF4FCB0FD83FCE3" authority="(Penny, 1982)" baseAuthorityName="Penny" baseAuthorityYear="1982" box="[347,617,853,879]" class="Insecta" family="Mantispidae" genus="Leptomantispa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ariasi" status="n. comb">
<emphasis id="B923EAC95C6DFFBEFEF4FCB0FE54FCE2" box="[347,446,853,878]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">L. ariasi</emphasis>
(Penny, 1982)
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B923EAC95C6DFFBEFDDEFCB0FD3EFCE3" bold="true" box="[625,724,853,879]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A21057B25C6DFFBEFDDEFCB0FD3EFCE3" box="[625,724,853,879]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" rank="species">n. comb</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C574D585C6DFFBEFCA2FCB0FBD1FCE3" authority="(Navas, 1908)" baseAuthorityName="Navas" baseAuthorityYear="1908" box="[781,1083,853,879]" class="Insecta" family="Mantispidae" genus="Leptomantispa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="axillaris" status="n. comb.">
<emphasis id="B923EAC95C6DFFBEFCA2FCB0FC67FCE2" box="[781,909,853,878]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">L. axillaris</emphasis>
(Navás, 1908)
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A21057B25C6DFFBEFBEDFCB0FB47FCE2" box="[1090,1197,853,879]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B923EAC95C6DFFBEFBEDFCB0FB4FFCE3" bold="true" box="[1090,1189,853,879]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">n. comb</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
